modules.description: Provides functions for measuring and manipulating time, including getting the current time, calculating durations, and converting between time representations. Works with types such as `Time.t` for timestamp values and `Time.Span.t` for time intervals. Used to track elapsed time in network protocols and schedule periodic tasks in Unix-based MirageOS applications.

Provides a blocking sleep operation with nanosecond precision, accepting an unsigned 64-bit integer to specify duration. Operates on raw time values and integrates with Lwt for asynchronous control flow. Used to introduce precise delays in real-time or event-driven applications.
